INSERT INTO `reviews` VALUES (1,1,'Annmarie Skinner','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100751983058143570475/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJokXmoIc1aZIw61teOBf7ng2D5r2kUXGuqp3NHCXySOxDKeQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo',5,'Went here today with my 4 daughters, ages 15, 18, 20 and 26. We had a fab time. My youngest especially enjoyed it and interacted throughout. Yes it’s a little out the way, but the trams are really easy to navigate to and from the centre, and cheap too! We got an uber there to ensure we wasn’t late, then tram into the city to explore some more. Was a nice couple hours spent siding something different. Staff are super friendly and helpful too.','2025-10-02 20:36:57','Google','2025-12-12 10:11:48'),(2,1,'Jenny Sun','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116859530143438484891/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXdYCBwY7fKwmVTQvSsihXXOT4BimrE8V22PI7FNot7pgnA82a3=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',5,'Went to Amaze with a friend and it was such a fun experience! We were just goofing around and loved the vibes. The rooms are really cool with lights, sounds, and lasers. It was different than we expected but in a good way. We got tickets on discount which made it even better. It’s probably a one-time fun thing, but definitely worth checking out if you want something unique in Amsterdam!\n\nAlso don’t go if you have epilepsy.','2025-09-05 12:55:33','Google','2025-12-12 10:11:48'),(3,1,'Zea Cuervo','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101241552088271842939/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUeKyFFIgQjZmMHhUL073Bbf2Vj1oKL3pYoRPNqcCDqfMju2kU=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2',5,'A must do in Amsterdam. The best place for someone who appreciates art, electronic music and visuals. Every room felt like a different part of a dream.\n\nStaff are really the best and the cocktails are a must try. The neon sour cocktail and the Amaze liquor, super recommended.\n\nThanks to ID&T for creating these kind of spaces.','2025-10-16 16:27:03','Google','2025-12-12 10:11:48'),(4,1,'Andres Hernandez','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101047718060416649382/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU_-sQLxgeKWy_i05gPgObiT-2vOS19QovbJJkTpNWNbhdmGHnQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo',5,'The best place to really understand rave culture. Amazing staff. I would have spent all my day here.\n\nI can’t stress enough how awesome and kind the staff are. Thank you so much guys.','2025-10-16 15:58:19','Google','2025-12-12 10:11:48'),(5,1,'Klara Pehar','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117169716056585365240/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXDy7Mo63YazKJ1QebO5uwPLHIa-5JUXP57Lj3vi744b2Zi6K0i=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo',5,'I went with my parents — one of the coolest activities you can do in Amsterdam! 🙌🏻🙌🏻\nIt’s basically an interactive light and laser show, accompanied by amazing sound and music.\nThe experience is set up across several rooms, and you move from one to the next without knowing what to expect. Each space is a surprise — and every one is unique, fun, and super immersive. I won’t go into too much detail so it stays a surprise for you!\nIf you’ve got an hour or an hour and a half of free time, definitely check it out.\nIt’s great for kids, adults, and even older visitors. Just a heads-up: it’s not recommended for people with epilepsy, as the lights and effects could trigger seizures.\n\nWill go again, once I come back in Ams💙','2025-10-21 09:00:27','Google','2025-12-12 10:11:48'),(6,2,'Marcus Lam','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110419576629097892078/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXUuBFJBAH1VnBooWCbRLucr32OsxWshhyqlexd_HtDHGhbCUKxrA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',5,'I loved it! I’m grateful for the entirely enclosed boat because it was raining.\n\nThe early boat at 9am was practically empty and a lovely start to the day. The review of the audio guide will vary depending on your taste. Yes, it was sparse, but for me it’s quite nice to not listen lots of info compared to a museum. It’s funny how walking along the canals that I was able to remember quite a few details from the tour! I suggest if you want a comprehensive tour to book elsewhere.\n\nOn this particular route, I found sitting on the left to be the best spot.','2025-10-30 10:16:23','Google','2025-12-12 10:12:33'),(7,2,'Sofia Maksimenko','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110684374445872107322/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLS--NJpGMoJUUIyDuXM9hq1DkrMGenjVyP10b0xmksNSKzFQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo',5,'We had a Wine Cheese 1.5 hours cruise on Satuday night. Such a lovely experience! I can\'t say we really could see a lot from the boat in a dark, but as a relaxing evening date it was just perfect. Comfortable warm boat, delicious bites and generous amount of wine (4 types were offered). Light music and super nice tem! Absolutely recommended.','2025-11-24 21:37:38','Google','2025-12-12 10:12:33'),(8,2,'Ben Clements','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114072496212248289629/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUj9K3FLdfo8ajZAT8-kq2cVOOhbrDOHwirQ7tmSeWSfO_EaD2J=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3',5,'Enjoyable boat tour around the canals of Amsterdam. We went with a different tour operator last time we were here, so chose Lovers for a different experience. It’s also included in the I Amsterdam pass, which is a bonus. The captain / tour guide was both informative and entertaining. Good sense of humour. Headphones included for the narrator which comes in several languages. Highly recommended.','2025-10-29 07:56:43','Google','2025-12-12 10:12:33'),(9,2,'aiyana samano','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108495609551462546426/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIME7QldhNKJieABu66CJG3RPboNVWy6NavZaRQlsh1GFMTkQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',3,'It was definitely a great experience seeing Amsterdam from the canals and exploring the different places through the canal tour. The tour itself was pretty informative and our host was enthusiastic and explaining all the different places across the locations within the river, it was a good experience to get to know the history of Amsterdam through this tour. It can be slightly uncomfortable though having to constantly look up from quite a low angle and the sides of the windows were mouldy and full of dirt, which made the experience less enjoyable. Definitely a tourist sort of activity and a one and done experience but still enjoyed it.','2025-08-25 06:18:03','Google','2025-12-12 10:12:33'),(10,2,'Miraj Mehta','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100703709399825125890/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJcUVIx2D0j86YTzD-CkWcGcjwwAayh3g_nzlbjGBQOrjx6wYwq=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5',3,'Better to go with an open boat to take pictures else sit on front row for closed top as they semi open the top from the front. Overall good canal tour.  3 star for a recorded guide instead of live fun guide on other cruises.','2025-10-30 07:25:39','Google','2025-12-12 10:12:33'),(11,3,'Jatin Khodiar','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108190729923183217438/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK5Q5poJGI7hKQylWZldUOBvUr0Gpu_bWr1yzSfSeYqbvXoKgcl=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2',5,'Had a great time at Amsterdam Dungeons! The whole experience was fun, interactive, and really well put together. I got picked to play the witch at the end and was chosen for another scene too, which made it even more memorable. The actors were brilliant, and the price felt fair for what you get. Definitely recommend it if you\'re in Amsterdam!','2025-07-22 18:27:56','Google','2025-12-12 10:13:16'),(12,3,'Kieran','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112724221494686846483/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVi7KvfSTcVIBzEdiFzaBm-pyd0JWjw1DOTGma1cUXPRLvplBTv=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',5,'A really fun experience, all the live actors were fantastic and fitted there roles well. Really good value for the price would definitely recommend a visit. My only complaint would be it did feel the group was too big and not enough sits for a few of the acts felt cramped in places.','2025-11-15 12:09:44','Google','2025-12-12 10:13:16'),(13,3,'Faith Rohani','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112627499636428343452/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUXZfDZjyXy3o-qf7ufvTtO-MNPwy1Cg47Mja3pleMAuBpJ4P5JUA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5',5,'Information before the fun stuff, the address given takes you to a door that then tells you to go around the building a bit more and yes. For us, we got sent to a random bar, and then we had to refind the address and use that lol.\n\nNo photos allowed during the tour, but it was good, you get truly engulfed into the stories.\n\nOh this was nice, informational, fun, interactive, funny and scary (if you get spooked easily) they pick people within the small groups to have you act out stuff, and there\'s signs and such for the chosen ones to do to make the storyline better. The actors were amazing, the group i had within it was fun, and i was chosen by my cousin as a woman who was accused to witchcraft, and needed to be burned at the stake. There were signs and such to tell me to scream and act like i was being burned alive to make the story more alive. Afterwards, i got a little fun paper, and the actor told me i did amazing and to go ahead and rejoin the group. Anywayz overall, great experience.','2025-06-24 20:53:08','Google','2025-12-12 10:13:16'),(14,3,'Nirvesh Seedeehul','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106178666719705793035/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWUog_b2hrZ4CIrodXgEquC_SqQtutrBl-0yFX0GsmI7MU69uiX=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2',5,'Amazing experience. You can tell the actors r very passionate about what they\'re doing and overall the experience was really fun. My fav part has to be at the last story, won\'t spoil but the way it was, was so realistic you\'d think u were actually in a horror movie','2025-10-01 05:41:30','Google','2025-12-12 10:13:16'),(15,3,'Eman AlGhamdi','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105137132636310809354/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXhfVoTC59PFUSCVOGrsGwis4BtQLEE7tM9ua40xawxCvIzQQ7K=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',5,'We had such an amazing time at Dungeon Amsterdam! The whole experience was a perfect mix of scary, funny, and surprising. We got genuinely spooked at times, laughed a ton, and were totally amazed by the actors and the atmosphere. The storytelling, sets, and jump scares were all so well done. Highly recommend if you’re looking for something fun and different to do in Amsterdam!','2025-11-22 07:34:04','Google','2025-12-12 10:13:16'),(16,4,'Aisha Patel','https://plus.google.com/112345678901234567890','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ALm5uY7i7JqR8xW9z_xYZ8k9q8q8s7tU9v7654321',5,'Absolutely loved wandering through the Royal Mile! The architecture is stunning and there\'s something interesting around every corner. Definitely worth spending at least a full day exploring.','2025-12-05 15:44:01','Gemini','2025-12-12 10:14:01'),(17,4,'Jean-Pierre Dubois','https://plus.google.com/109876543210987654321','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ALm5uY5j6k5l4h3g2f1e0d9c8b7a6z5y9x8w7v3u2',4,'Edinburgh Castle is a must-see, offering incredible views of the city. The history is fascinating, though it can get quite crowded, so try to go early in the morning to avoid the biggest queues.','2025-11-28 15:44:01','Gemini','2025-12-12 10:14:01'),(18,4,'Kimiko Tanaka','https://maps.google.com/?cid=9876543210987654321','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ALm5uY6l5k4j3i2h1g0f9e8d7c6b5a4z3x2w1v0u',5,'The atmosphere in the Old Town is magical. I especially enjoyed the traditional pubs with live music. The Scotch whisky experience was also a highlight!','2025-12-09 15:44:01','Gemini','2025-12-12 10:14:01'),(19,4,'David O\'Connell','https://www.facebook.com/profile.php?id=1234567890','https://scontent.xx.fbcdn.net/v/t1.0-9/12345678_1234567890_n.jpg?oh=1234567890abcdef1234567890abcdef&oe=12345678',4,'Great for a day trip. Lots of shops catering to tourists, but still retains a historic charm. The closes off the Royal Mile are worth exploring.','2025-11-12 15:44:01','Gemini','2025-12-12 10:14:01'),(20,4,'Maria Rodriguez','https://maps.google.com/?cid=8765432109876543210','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ALm5uY4k2j1i0h9g8f7e6d5c4b3a2z1y9x8w7v6u4',5,'We loved the Old Town! So much history and beautiful architecture. Walking around was like stepping back in time.','2025-11-28 15:44:01','Gemini','2025-12-12 10:14:01'),(21,5,'Mariam','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108226595155828583491/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW6OF2oEp0o5k6MzikMBmuJdv0Dm3UTaglDLm1O1Vua-DACvXp9=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba8',5,'Palace of Holyroodhouse is a beautiful and majestic place located at the end of the Royal Mile. It’s one of Edinburgh’s most important historic landmarks, offering visitors a fascinating glimpse into Scotland’s royal history. The palace features stunning architecture, elegant rooms, and lovely gardens that add to its charm. However, photography is not allowed in most of the rooms to protect the historic artifacts and furnishings. Despite that, the visit is truly worth it — the atmosphere, details, and royal elegance make it an unforgettable experience.','2025-12-06 22:26:10','Google','2025-12-12 10:14:27'),(22,5,'Victoria Molloy','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/118292329183123671686/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIRVZHJqSUv9UKFHGMxJLvIPBa4QmbEajJnZFQ90TyTGMhQ2DU=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3',5,'I really enjoyed exploring this palace and the audio guide included with the ticket was very informative to learn about Scottish history and the tour is well laid out. The great gallery room was very impressive!','2025-11-25 19:04:08','Google','2025-12-12 10:14:27'),(23,5,'Margaret O\' Sullivan','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108869876892176355551/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUFVZR1AI8S9KEBO_R-ljXu27wWLlYWRFwXcqYDIgnr-RDFbpevig=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo',5,'I loved being able to walk around at my own pace listening to the audio guide. Loved learning about the history and the kings/queens who lived there.\nNo photos allowed inside. Beautiful gardens also and a café.','2025-10-21 17:58:05','Google','2025-12-12 10:14:27'),(24,5,'Ftse','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/118359534622794219504/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJJcKUl53KJMUuKrHXHnp11lULsFvZ-uhpEk8ru35IsYej6ew=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5',5,'This was definitely worth a visit. Yes, it does cost to go in but the handset made it worthwhile as they had an interactive app that helped the kids to learn, search and play. Out of all the historic sites we went to, they learnt the most at this site. The palace was beautiful and well maintained. There was one area (tight staircase heading to Mary\'s room) that would be an issue to get to for those who struggle to walk upstairs. There was no signage to provide another route. Other than that, we had a fabulous time and my 3 kids aged from 7 to 14 all enjoyed it.\n\nAll in all, a breathtaking','2025-10-29 09:55:23','Google','2025-12-12 10:14:27'),(25,5,'Christopher Notya','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110917857696601528878/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLusl4IJct9K0KUArazfxcULxZTUezyu_E0l13zUfmweUG4sg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo',5,'Really cool place to visit! You get to walk through real royal rooms and learn lots of interesting stories (the audio guide is super helpful). The palace feels grand but still very peaceful, and the gardens are beautiful too. A perfect stop if you want a mix of history and chill vibes in Edinburgh.','2025-11-14 09:29:57','Google','2025-12-12 10:14:27'),(26,6,'Lianne Brouwer','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102388106487172163178/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIBAq2rDT3oe17Mlk08VDuWvLz6WohtZKA0-le7eGUrfKB4mQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo',5,'Great tour! It was very interesting and impressive to hear about the history of the close, and to walk through the actual remains. Our guide Sam was absolutely amazing. He was a great storyteller. Charismatic, and incredibly engaging.\nIf you\'re in Edinburgh, don\'t skip this tour, it is 100% worth it!','2025-11-13 22:15:33','Google','2025-12-12 10:15:10'),(27,6,'Ido Michel','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110382316013977176643/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK2y6_3BrVj0QHsdKDsa2748dHhPisgGrFWuv5i1sWadwX4Ld4=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5',5,'Very interesting visit. Great insight on the past in Edinburgh.\nIt is a guided tour. Our guide was Lorraine and she did a great.\nThe tour is one hour tour. I went with my son almost 13 years old and it was not too scary.\nDefinitely, a must visit in Edinburgh.','2025-10-10 18:13:50','Google','2025-12-12 10:15:10'),(28,6,'Karmen','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100549348478228671601/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ3j1GkarboeoWjR6_fm-jsVPvdmsQ1EdwOHufijIERLDb0IA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3',5,'Great tour! Loved that the guide dresses up as someone from the time period and stays in character too. Our guide Daisy was so charismatic and passionate. Her enunciation was a 10/10 too. If you\'re thinking of buying the plague doctor mask keychain at the gift shop, note that it doesn’t actually come with the key ring, you only get the charm itself!','2025-10-13 16:00:43','Google','2025-12-12 10:15:10'),(29,6,'Brooke Hunter','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101531789665384640586/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLuw4pZkU4GmVNlNUJMCFHfXu7f_DPRcyxrLX6sZlmAL7OK5w=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo',5,'My second time doing The Real Mary Kings Close tour and I loved it even more this time. Such a highlight this tour, one of the best things to do in Edinburgh. Our tour guide\nAnthony was brilliant, he made the tour. I will be back for another tour when I come back to Edinburgh I love this place so much.','2025-10-21 20:07:15','Google','2025-12-12 10:15:10'),(30,6,'Karina Wall','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117779608029221356859/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocItBdQYH9EyTvmExv9aETQ8YgfYPrNAQPUjCA36urrIICpQrQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2',5,'We pre-booked this tour ahead of our short trip to Edinburgh, and we are so glad we did.\nVery easy to find and very fascinating to find out about the Close and seeing the underground world of the city.\nOur tour guide, Sam Wise, was very knowledgeable and explained the history along with being entertaining too.\nIf your visiting Edinburgh , this is a must!','2025-11-23 07:37:43','Google','2025-12-12 10:15:10'),(31,7,'Timothy Cheung','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101189268452984469478/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUG5_OQvDzg1mMMtzIQzZZLeUbBkIEWdltAkHVM1aC4jJmBc98uIA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2',5,'The Mob Museum absolutely exceeded our expectations! Every exhibit was incredibly well thought out — informative, immersive, and engaging from start to finish. You can tell a lot of care went into curating the history on both sides of organized crime and law enforcement rather than glamorizing it, which made the experience feel powerful and authentic.\n\nOne of the highlights for me was the educational section about law enforcement use of force. It tackled a serious topic in a respectful and factual way, giving insight into how split-second decisions are made in real situations. The scenario simulator was intense (in a good way!) and gave a whole new appreciation for how challenging that profession really is.\n\nWe walked out feeling entertained, educated, and impressed. You don’t just look at history here — you experience it. If you’re in Vegas and want something meaningful and memorable beyond the casinos, The Mob Museum is a must-see. I’d absolutely go again!','2025-12-02 17:33:22','Google','2025-12-12 10:15:55'),(32,7,'Nataku','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101420810389294015497/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWTzskMbQB0w89T5WGeHN_9JfdRAFGi_NN5gAmVz5ws_WZLnRQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo',5,'I actually spent three hours here and I’m surprised that I spent so long in here because I didn’t expect this place to be so interesting. They had this mobster guy talking for 45 minutes. He also had the tasting downstairs of whiskey and it was good because they actually explained everything about the whiskey although I found it too long. That was also very informative as well. You have a cool speak easy downstairs make sure to go behind the painting because there’s a secret room there. make sure you check online for coupons. I got a 20% off coupon online.','2025-11-11 02:51:44','Google','2025-12-12 10:15:55'),(33,7,'J Joyner','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105547909881988222546/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKyatthlOLo_P9RD0neyAOBgEAUxwBmnSZY-BR_x3LgTSLBQQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',5,'Loved this attraction. Was busier than I anticipated.  Go in the late afternoon...if you want to actually view the exhibits. Vegas is NOT dead! Interesting exhibits. We purchased the additional attractions for the distillery tasting and Interactive shooting scenario. My advice with live scenario, shoot first ask questions later!!  The distillery was great experience. Purchased a few travel sized bottles!!','2025-10-27 22:04:08','Google','2025-12-12 10:15:55'),(34,7,'Marika Lyons','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117568287176430613897/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJlFDefrVmhEBdxa2lsaJ9moyUlAfj5PzPGTI1dbP2YiHEf0EU=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5',5,'I picked two museums to go to while in Vegas for three days. The Mob Museum was one of them so fun! You can spend 3 hours or more in here. I will be back when I am in town. I want to check out The Underground Speakeasy and Distillery speakeasy. It was so cool down there. My niece and I did one interactive experience Firearm Training Stimulator. Wow! What a great experience we had. The gift shop is a must even if you\'re just looking. I did buy a T-shirt.','2025-11-15 02:25:00','Google','2025-12-12 10:15:55'),(35,7,'Daniel Trevino','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105170786480935269358/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX0g8SMcDR3Zcr2aczaL9_wJkpQ4sC2L1TflHbRF3V18FG498Qg9Q=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',5,'Such an awesome museum with so many activities and history about the mob, Vegas, and the legacy of where it is today.\nI highly recommend the shooting experience, you can find out how great of a shot you are in real high stress scenarios.\nDefinitely worth every penny!! Next time we\'re bringing the kids.','2025-12-06 02:25:55','Google','2025-12-12 10:15:55'),(36,8,'shellintheshell shell','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102492561719902260741/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX_QrBvBLrABojxeySo0zF4THcdGvBHAAWvFW9YZar6Nfh-vOjw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',5,'We are vacationing here from Texas and we always make it point to visit as many museums as we can. This one did not disappoint! Great staff! Wonderful exhibits! We made it in time for the shark feeding and we really enjoyed it! Animatronic dinos were really cool! This is a must for museum lovers! They have a really great Egyptian exhibit! And don\'t forget to visit Africa! Last but not least, the marine section of the museum ! Great visit all around! 10/10! This museum will be on my top 5 list! Will visit again!','2025-06-27 17:46:16','Google','2025-12-12 10:16:32'),(37,8,'Jean White','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114266811502628853468/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjViAhfbfUdfJukv5xzmqVFRhczUzTKnFfihhlXOoQ8VlAA6nOM=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3',5,'🤩 took my family, for my son‘s birthday. And it was so nice so many cool things to look at and read about. I absolutely recommend this place. Definitely kid friendly. ♥︎','2025-08-14 01:31:16','Google','2025-12-12 10:16:32'),(38,8,'Ayla Blanchette','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101385242910891252475/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXMw8DhDZZR0YKn7R2rqtRUXUqJ30cbQoG-yCeUuaQleVWqoUw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo',5,'Amazing visit!\n\nI’m a Las Vegas local, so I’ve spent my childhood coming here, and the upgrades done to the museum recently are great! Low crowds, well priced tickets, and extensive exhibits. The volunteers are also very informative, especially in the dinosaur exhibit. I’m glad to see it’s been kept in amazing shape all these years.\n\nI enjoy coming back here frequently, even as an adult with no children. Thank you, Las Vegas Natural History museum, for great memories!','2025-10-07 20:31:51','Google','2025-12-12 10:16:32'),(39,8,'Sarah Foster','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100960361204477230004/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWicYBGQsOEyCBxwasZZcD-Y_cjcqMOHh_kZoiqTWPubBbIee4evw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2',5,'Although I do have young children, I am on a trip without them this week and wanted something to do in Vegas that wasn\'t a casino. I came across a discounted ticket for the natural history museum through a third party site for $9 and decided to go.\n\nAs a solo adult it took me about an hour to walk through all the exhibits. I imagine if I would have had my children with me, it would have been closer to 3 hours.\n\nI found each exhibit interesting, but especially enjoyed the replica of King Tut\'s tomb.\n\nThe museum staff were all very nice and it was also super cool to meet an archeologist in the lab downstairs working on fossils. Overall I\'d highly recommend coming here, with or without children :)','2025-03-11 18:16:01','Google','2025-12-12 10:16:32'),(40,8,'Carter “Grandpa” Skillman','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103142571587074766448/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVqK8ueFrdjLJt-BtmeARpHmC3L-TpNNCAys4ppyvfKzHi5wvb-=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-