ll enjoyment. Highly recommend this tour for the amazing views and cultural entertainment!','2025-07-13 21:36:30','Google','2025-12-12 10:21:08'),(75,15,'Jamie Wemken','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113219985780618736940/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVOmeGCaLc9QkMR9DCEtzvcWiooL0rbM9hbGUKqUj9tJ-f7brs6=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3',4,'Fun experience. Our guide was knowledgeable and amusing. It\'s best to arrive early if you want a good seat with a view. The drink prices were about what you would expect. The bbq dinner was average, the weight staff was friendly, and service was quick.\n\nCons: There was no air flow on the boat, so sitting on it for 30+ mins in the heat waiting for departure, surrounded by 100 people got hot and smelly. It would have been nice if they had fans to circulate the air. Cup holders on the seats would have been beneficial. Also, the bathroom stalls were very snug.\nOverall we had a great time and I would recommend the tour','2025-09-01 12:53:12','Google','2025-12-12 10:21:08'),(76,16,'Juliya Kurlyanchik','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100249555959764474224/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX_ZOyJecrnLK7y-u0IQZ7miBLmQbrCwIkuw1XuQI04yRsG2RHyhg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6',5,'Such an amazing experience! The installations were absolutely stunning — bright, detailed, and incredibly realistic. We loved it, even though the weather was a bit chilly and the drive took us about an hour each way.\n\nI highly recommend arriving at least three hours before closing, because two hours definitely weren’t enough for us. Everything is so vibrant and picturesque. A wonderful experience, even after the main safari area had already closed!','2025-11-29 05:39:24','Google','2025-12-12 10:21:48'),(77,16,'Sarah Westleigh-Soldano','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112254062978459170052/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUs9cuoJDNqiv_QdSi3-KR4VeYrMUcFNsXdjyHhI0WzD_o2rUCK=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3',5,'What an incredible safari tour! With so many animals to view it was well worth the admission cost. When driving through, you receive (at your wish) a voice guided tour that you can get scanning the qr code which provides you with facts and history of each animal within the park. What makes this park even more incredible, is you can walk through another park where you view birds, flamingos, giraffes and go on a boat tour (extra fee). There is a small amusement park along with gorgeous flowers and fascinating decorative paths to walk through. Definitely a place for those between 2-120 years!!!!','2025-11-01 01:16:50','Google','2025-12-12 10:21:48'),(78,16,'Ben L','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111578011996670969104/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWAdBhi7uGYZho0qqotdxgkqdc36reszLUpgRgn0rGsqi1oTK-N=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',5,'We love Lion Country Safari! It’s such an amazing place to bring the family and friends. You are allowed to respectfully drive through the park and take in the surreal sights of the diverse array of animals and habitats. You can take your time to truly appreciate everything that’s available. Once you’re done driving through the safari, you can spend some time at the park to continue to observe Gods creatures, grab a snack, let the kiddos play at the waterpark, or purchase some souvenirs. I highly recommend spending a day at the Safari.','2025-10-18 18:48:33','Google','2025-12-12 10:21:48'),(79,16,'Stephen Toth','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115004728078584979927/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUwm0P79f2oAfq9BqQdDHTYRw2qpcJNWx1QD5VDz7IZNwx_6btR=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',4,'There\'s a nice variety of animals to look at during the visit with an informative audio guide that\'s pleasant to listen to while you drive through the safari.  Don\'t expect the animals to \"perform\" for you. This is a natural environment very similar to their own. Most of what you see is grazing, though you might get some interaction. But that\'s the point of a preserve, to see the animals as undisturbed as possible. Very well suited for children with fun stuff to do after the tour.','2025-12-02 12:18:28','Google','2025-12-12 10:21:48'),(80,16,'kevin velasquez','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117346150682939356771/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXbWxVOcqTB9lNHg3FPjOY3F-XyiplAGp7hLNcn1NWjv6kHO0M=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo',5,'It was a nice visit! Although I would like to have had the windows down the animals didn’t seem interested in approaching our vehicles but we had our windows up, it was nice to drive through once and walk around we did the feeding and petting area we enjoyed the boat tour and the maze. We didn’t eat there but we stopped by a Mexican restaurant close by avanges or something like that. But it was a nice time we left there happy. Wasn’t too hot walking around we ran through splash pad but didn’t stay there’s','2025-10-19 12:12:49','Google','2025-12-12 10:21:48'),(81,17,'Holly P','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104539674559380055507/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUy6scwe-KTZzx0_0-yUKtuiZZj-JkKIfDoCcatywj3AeMHXL_aRg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6',5,'The catacombs of Paris are great for history buffs, people who love architecture, people who love morbid or creepy stuff, people who are are spiritual or religious, and anyone interested in learning about the truth behind Paris history. Definitely worth the trip to see, it’s amazing to see how such a dense city grapples with the limited space and demands of a large population. Absolutely reminds you of how human you are. Definitely worth booking a private tour. Audioguides are only €6 and you can reserve on site, but I booked a tour guide. Awesome trip. Loved seeing the altar and Christian artworks and crosses. May all of the souls in the Catacombs rest in peace.','2025-10-30 20:26:54','Google','2025-12-12 10:21:55'),(82,17,'Jamie Higgs-Dey','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115763750949592100729/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVRMXceQCm8O28O98PGW5cI7QOPsvq_farl_08KcK06VWOMOZd5=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6',5,'The labyrinth of limestone is fascinating, everyone buried together without hierarchy is humbling and to walk through and experience this is very unique. A must do when you’re in Paris. The process of finding and creating the catacombs is also incredible.\nGreat self-guided tour, the audio guide is detailed enough to give you plenty of info without being boring or too lengthy.\nThe queue system for the different time slots works well. Staff were helpful.\nI would highly recommend this, it’s not too far away from the centre, if you like walking you could walk there or just take a quick ride on the metro. We booked tickets in advance and they were rather limited as it’s so popular.','2025-11-09 14:27:59','Google','2025-12-12 10:21:55'),(83,17,'B S','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/118374009318834529273/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLwiaItsu881S69bJVzZOknPUjGBtqPnso4MWqNAWIxwz0DPw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6',5,'Excellent place to visit, on the day of visting, I noticed at 11am all the tickets for the day were sold out for the Friday,  so it\'s worth getting a ticket in advance. It\'s organised well from the way the scheduled times are filtered to the quick security checks. The audio machines are high quality and easy to use, they are available in different languages. Security is tight and there are frequent visits by security within the catacombs as the greatest damage is actually done by people touching the bones.  There were over 6 million people\'s bones here and here there was no hierarchy so poor people could have been next to the rich. It is sad that this catacomb was discovered as houses caved in due to the underground void leading to the discovery. The tickets can be booked directly from the place and in this instance there is no need for a guide as the guide cannot jump the queue and its a one way system, full price with an audio guide is 31 euros, 25 euros for reduced price, and 12 for people aged 5 to 17 years, it is expensive in comparison to other sites like the Eiffel Tower or the Lourve. Note the catacombs will shut from 03 Nov 2025 to spring 2026. Tickets can be booked 7 days in advance.\nThe visitor entrance is located at the following address:\n1, Avenue du Colonel Henri Rol-Tanguy (place Denfert-Rochereau)\n75014 Paris. There is a limit on the size of bag that can be taken (40×30cm), no strollers tripods etc are allowed. Flash photography is allowed so long as it doesn\'t cause issues to other  guests. The place is limited to 200 per day and it is not encouraged to visit if you have mobility issues, there are 131 steps going down and 112 to ascend, some places are slippery so care must be taken, the walk is 1.5km and can take an hour to negotiate.','2025-10-17 05:57:29','Google','2025-12-12 10:21:55'),(84,17,'Ariel Jewel','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111418563977977305187/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXUJ20t0qJGLqLr2ghrJAuGNAubPfRtHyQozXLFo3nbAVdJl5A=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5',5,'as someone who loves horror (hello as above so below) I adored the catacombs. it’s located in a random little square in the middle of the streets, and upon entering you climb down 10m of stairs, where the vistable portion of the catacombs starts and is laid out like a museum. I loved this format, it made the visit so much more immersive. note that floors can be slippery though.\n\nIn each area of the catacombs there’s a free audio guide piece and an information board on the history of the catacombs, and also certain engravings on the walls that are highlighted including dates and words from more than a hundred years ago. I also liked that the place wasn’t absolutely teeming with people and that there were still areas where you could be alone with the ambiance.\n\nhonestly walking silently, 20m below ground, through the mountains of bones and remains is so cool and unique and memorable?? there was also a guide there who was absolutely stellar at her work, and who provided detailed information of the catacombs and current restoration works.\n\nmy dumb ahh also bumped straight into a skull and promptly gave myself a heart attack so there’s THAT\n\ngift shop is also super fun!','2025-11-24 20:10:35','Google','2025-12-12 10:21:55'),(85,17,'Penny Gaffney','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100865124178850645279/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWb80s2guqAoj8ime63oMCAX6_Lzk1OrW6MONXDsebhyFJJo377iQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba8',5,'One of those fascination all human has with dead thing and to see it in such a volume is fascinating!\nI visited the Catacombs of Paris in my first time to Paris in 2018 and this place was the most standout from that time so when I had a chance to come back to Paris again this was the only place I wanted to revisit. (And the cheese fondue restaurant)\nI think they might have lower a cap number of people in each time slot now since when I tried to book tickets most of the time slots are all sold out and only a couple left for the 2 days I was in Paris.\nIt was also very quiet and not many people down there. It was super nice to be able to take your time to walked around and look at things slowly! I really enjoyed that 💀\nI didn\'t see the skull coin souvenir last time so I was so glad to get some magnet and coin this time! 🪙☠️\nThe staff was very friendly and professional! Great gift shop at the finish of the tunnel!\nSomehow I blocked out information about the 300 spirel stairs to go down into the tunnel and come back up from last time, got a bit dizzy 🥴 going down too fast 😂\nDefinitely a recommendation of thing to do in Paris.','2025-11-16 10:32:05','Google','2025-12-12 10:21:55'),(86,18,'Geoffrey Caron-Lormier','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104896848385424420159/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQkYBP6vEbySF0YmByac8sifoKEBUZokIh7j91X-46kWP6PSyXLg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5',5,'A good experience. Small but well populated with a good range of animals, including a manatee which we had not seen before.\n\nWe spent 4h30 on site, including a quick lunch and the little shop at the end.\n\nThe enclosures looked big enough for the animals.\n\nOverall, we enjoyed and likely to go back at some point, reminded us of the London Zoo.','2025-10-31 16:03:17','Google','2025-12-12 10:22:53'),(87,18,'Rana O.','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114020945902660374977/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLRN7-Y-mwJTwBgfQvtuTGvjIBi8X7Pm6dyCLEFgdi7IHc48rw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6',5,'We have spent 3 hours exploring the zoo. We enjoyed our time. The zoo route is clear and guides u easily between animals. It contains a good variety of animals & birds. It could have been great if there were an elephant and bear.\nA recommendation for sure!','2025-07-22 08:39:17','Google','2025-12-12 10:22:53'),(88,18,'Laura Grieve','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107397444383511756787/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLRpLxr-0lKuFsHSF_16krxK5l1LO6xXy1eJQ78c6w86KcOGg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',5,'Brillant zoo. Lovely  enclosures, staff were very helpful. All animals looked well maintained. Terrible weather and the zoo closed for safety and we were given a full refund. Didnt make the gift shop so my teddy collection is short 🤣 great morning out no crowds','2025-10-27 19:23:50','Google','2025-12-12 10:22:53'),(89,18,'Vincent M','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/118365014739243027327/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW9NuzuiayqcaXweoG9kQsTF_y5DilaY2eLls1vateFWu132wb7=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',5,'An amazing Zoo, with many animals and a lot to explore. My favorite points were:\nThe big bird aviary where the birds can fly over, next you.\nThe tropical greenhouse\nThe savannah area where only a water feature and an electric fence seems to separate visitors from the animals.','2025-11-11 12:32:27','Google','2025-12-12 10:22:53'),(90,18,'Maddie D','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113095243651841836803/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL640PbAACXMrjO5goOvy2Z_v5trvzWwEyRt--oX2OVrfQB1A=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3',5,'Easily one of the best zoos I have been to. Went on a day where it was rainy midday and the zoo was nearly empty. We had great weather and the animals were awake and active. The enclosures seemed like they had planets of space for the animals within them and the animals seemed content, which made me happy.','2025-07-25 15:14:04','Google','2025-12-12 10:22:53'),(91,19,'Dr Robert Nash','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102993876013775611461/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVhD4_YBsV-D0HlPJ8OqvCLqdP4DvYzCeN7s1uynS6RhAEObLVj1A=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo',5,'A very old, interesting, and wonderful cemetery.\nWalking through the cemetery gives you a tour of both history and art.  I highly recommend it.  It would be easy to spend an afternoon here.','2025-12-05 17:54:47','Google','2025-12-12 10:23:47'),(92,19,'julie demdam','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103348019379082804349/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU91YZc2gBzRVDSGV7oB8mrrta5ct-x15qsWBAMAeFWemgfia7e=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5',5,'Of my 5 visits to Paris, I’ve been here 3 times. This most current visit was the quickest as it started to rain as soon as we entered.\n\nOur biggest mistake was not taking a photo of the map as soon as we entered. We ended up bumping into a couple of Americans with a map so we ended up getting a snap of theirs.\nWe didn’t really have a solid plan. All I knew was that I wanted to see Jimmy and that’s it. We ended up on quite the adventure finding Jimmy. It seemed like we walked in circles.\nThe great thing about this cemetery is that there are so many famous people interred here. And many notable families. With that said, you’ll see some elaborate tombstones.\nYou do see a few employees walking the grounds. They all walk around during closing time, ringing their bells to let you know they’re about to close so you better skidaddle or you’ll be locked in.\nI’m going to do a walking tour the next time I’m in town so I can cover more ground. I’m always so overwhelmed when I’m there\nIt is however super sad to see the graves that are clearly unattended, sometimes looking like they’ve been abandoned.','2025-10-20 00:19:28','Google','2025-12-12 10:23:47'),(93,19,'Carl Fulghieri','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108288912145836256119/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUrphoBf7rDhcRYpJJrTGsp7Dgqorzq01Qfq7_ZElD_T2MUuwB4=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3',5,'A good site to visit in Paris. There are many interred here who have influenced and inspired you — even if you don’t know it yet. During peak tourist season there are a number of friendly attendants to provide maps and directions. Toilets are in the south. Some accessibility concerns: many ways are cobbled and some steep, although there is a slope going around the whole cemetery.','2025-10-09 20:50:40','Google','2025-12-12 10:23:47'),(94,19,'Trouvaille B','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103591100681277977228/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUhxHckC3MHsxSXPM93V-J07afnLSJ3TCkK6F63-F5UXEAGYpf7UQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5',5,'This cemetery was so great, I ended up going twice. Some of the headstones are so amazing, you have to just walk around and see where you end up. If I could have spent a day here, I would have.\n\nI do understand that headstones are close together and probably difficult to maintain, but in some areas, the weeds are so tall and areas are overgrown :(','2025-09-19 19:08:18','Google','2025-12-12 10:23:47'),(95,19,'Martin K.','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102818011791033311662/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWC8OpmDugjj4N_OXg4CVEY-9yXg7SzSEgeX4StoBbljHtKPWCt=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba7',5,'The counterpoint to the glittering Parisian boulevards.\nDefinitely worth a visit at any time of year, but especially outside the summer months. The gloomier the weather, the more beautiful it becomes. Creates a sense of closeness to people you have never known.\nEvery grave tells its own story of transience, sorrow, but also creativity and inspiration.\nTake your time, you can easily spend a couple of hours here.\nIt\'s best to give the Morrison tomb a wide berth, as any sense of reflection tends to be drowned out there.','2025-10-05 14:08:16','Google','2025-12-12 10:23:47');
